      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;Dear SOE,&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;Part of living in Australia is getting patches during our prime playing time, please, please, please patch at the time posted on EQ Live.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;A couple of weeks ago, my freinds and I all logged at 8pm (3am PDT) as this was the posted time of the patch, as we hadn't seen any warning messages I left my trader up and the patch didn't come through until 9pm, another LDoN mission missed or an AA or two in KT could have been had.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;Tonight, the patch is posted for 9pm (4am PDT) so we start a mission in N Ro at about 7:40, plenty of time to finish a normal adventure and camp out tidily before the patch. Five minute into the mission, along come the warnings that the server is going down at 8pm, not 9pm.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;Surely it can't be that hard for your techs to either look at the Network Status page before they shut us down, or post the correct time for patches there. Admittedly this is hardly the worst thing about EQ, and thank you for the fixes coming through, but a little attention to detail would go a long way.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
